<font color="#FF0000">A POEM (BADLY) FOR PEACE HERE</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 13 22:54:45 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
vets were true, but protestors were right,<br>
and men were men, in the darkest of night,<br>
men died, screamed, and were killed and whored,<br>
only to end up in front of their local draft board.<br><br>
the war, like a twister, changed us all,<br>
it unleashed the killer in some if not all,<br>
but for others, it made them introspect,<br>
and they could not kill, even an incect.<br><br>
so the war in nam raged, and death was the winner,<br>
and to the the soldiers, the peacenik's were the sinners,<br>
but the protestors knew their their cause was true,<br>
and they had a place, in the red, white, and blue.<br><br>
the war was a mistake, now we all can agree,<br>
from the men in the foxhole, to those that had to flee,<br>
but can we but it behind us, once and for all,<br>
and join arms, turn, salute the flag, one and all?<br><br>
cause this is america, a land where we all are free<br>
and the blood of patriots, and protesters, water the tree,<br>
freedom is a gift, so delicate and so strong,<br>
that there is no right, and never an wrong.<br><br>
so brothers and sisters, of the generation so swallowed,<br>
and to those, who may have lead, and those who followed,<br>
the time has come to lay it all to rest.<br>
these are my thoughts, to me, its all I have, the best.<br><br>
so to mom, and warrior, and sparrow hawk,<br>
I hope you learn, and do not gawk.<br>
for the many there are, on all sides now,<br>
and we come together, finally, and if we can...wow!!!<br><br>
After 30 years, it is time to &quot;love one another right now&quot;.<br><br>
silent protestor<br>

